17/03/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov said Thursday (17 March) that a draft resolution on the Bulgarian military's presence in Iraq would be prepared and submitted to parliament by the end of March. The document would address the issue of withdrawing the Bulgarian contingent after 2005. On Tuesday, President Georgi Parvanov officially called for a withdrawal, following a friendly fire fatality.
In other news, Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg is in Rabat, Morocco, where he has signed a number of agreements boosting bilateral co-operation. (bTV, Dnevnik, 24 Chasa - 17/03/05; Mediapool, Bulgarian government Web site - 16/03/05)
